    <note>Li(2) Sun [1034] Xiang(3) [19774], jinshi in 1063, is identified in Fujian TZ, 147.22b as Sun's younger brother, which is clearly an error since Xiang was Gao's [3512] younger brother and, therefore, Duo's [3536] son. This does, however, establish a documented link between Sun and the other Guangze Li(2) and TZ probably errs in identifying Sun as younger brother rather than grandfather. I am assuming that Sun was, therefore, Duo's father. Fujian TZ, 147.2b-3a; XCB, 75.14a, 14a (n.). CBD, 2, 875.</note>
